@sul007

Don't panic. Little SNithc is supposed to block programs from accessing the web. What you have to do is open Little Snitch Configurations, then create rules for your program to follow. THose rules determine which apps have access to the net and which don't. Everytime an app tries to access, you will be prompted to let it or not. At first you will have A LOT of those messages but once Little Snitch understands your preferences (always click Allow/Deny FOREVER) you won't have to worry about it. Make sure you deny all connections for pirated software and allow all for legal stuff.
